Ruling on burying a man in his mother 's grave
07 Nov 2019, 07:43 by Abdullah Saleem
Abdullah Salim ruled the burial of the man in the tomb of his mother .. Sheikh Ahmed Wissam, Secretary of Fatwa in Dar al-Ifta, said that burying the man in the grave where his mother was buried, noting, pointing out that if there is no possibility of a grave for each dead separately, the man is buried in Is it permissible for men and women to be buried in one cemetery when necessary? Asked Dr. Mufti, the Grand Mufti of the Republic, the author says: "Is it permissible to bury males with females in one cemetery if necessary? A woman was buried with a man who had died before in the same cemetery. ”Dr. Shawqi Allam replied, in a fatwa, that every dead person should be singled out It is true that the Prophet (peace and blessings of Allaah be upon him) used to combine the two men and three of one of the martyrs in one grave, and that men must have their own graves and women should have their own graves. Men and women are buried in one cemetery and there should be a brick barrier or a curtain of dust between men and women, said Sheikh Amr al-Wardani, secretary of the fatwa in the Egyptian Fatwa House, that the visit of women to the tombs, a prize and nothing, if they abide by the morals. Amin al-Fatwa, in answer to a question «Is visiting the cemeteries for women halal or h Or through the official page of the house, that the visit of women to the graves is halal, but if they adhere to the legal etiquette, where the Messenger of Allah peace be upon him ((not that I was the end of the three and then it seemed to me: the end of your visit Thy heart, and tears the eye, and remember the Hereafter, and visit them, and do not say abandonment ... Hadith;
